Package: blaze
Title: Strict Gradual Type Checking
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Brett", "Gilio", , "giliobrett@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: A strict, opt-in type system for existing R code. Types are
    written in ordinary R and enforced at runtime on function arguments,
    return values, vectors, and data frame columns. The checking engine
    is implemented in Rust for speed.
License: Apache License (>= 2)
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 8.0.0
Config/rextendr/version: 0.5.0
SystemRequirements: Cargo (Rust's package manager), rustc >= 1.85.0, xz
Depends:
    R (>= 4.2)
Imports:
    S7
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
